Class Type<T>

java.lang.Object
io.github.syst3ms.skriptparser.types.Type<T>
public class Type<T> extends Object
A basic definition of a type. This doesn't handle number (single/plural), unlike PatternType
See Also:

  • Constructor Details

    • Type

      public Type(Class<T> typeClass, String baseName, String pattern, Documentation documentation)
      Constructs a new Type.
      Parameters:
      typeClass - the class this type represents
      baseName - the basic name to represent this type with. It should be more or less a lowercase version of the Java class.
      pattern - the pattern for plural forms. It's written in Skript aliases plural format. Examples :
      • fish -> fish (invariant)
      • dog&brvbar;s -> dog and dogs
      • part&brvbar;y&brvbar;ies -> party and parties (irregular plural)

    • Type

      public Type(Class<T> typeClass, String baseName, String pattern, @Nullable @Nullable Function<String, ? extends T> literalParser, Documentation documentation, @Nullable @Nullable Supplier<Iterator<T>> supplier)
      Constructs a new Type.
      Parameters:
      typeClass - the class this type represents
      baseName - the basic name to represent this type with. It should be more or less a lowercase version of the Java class.
      pattern - the pattern for plural forms. It's written in Skript aliases plural format. Examples :
      • fish -> fish (invariant)
      • dog&brvbar;s -> dog and dogs
      • part&brvbar;y&brvbar;ies -> party and parties (irregular plural)
      literalParser - the function that would parse literals for the given type. If the parser throws an exception on parsing, it will be caught and the type will be ignored.

    • Type

      public Type(Class<T> typeClass, String baseName, String pattern, @Nullable @Nullable Function<String, ? extends T> literalParser, Function<? super T, String> toStringFunction, @Nullable @Nullable Function<? super T, String> toVariableNameFunction, Documentation documentation, @Nullable @Nullable Supplier<Iterator<T>> supplier)
      Constructs a new Type.
      Parameters:
      typeClass - the class this type represents
      baseName - the basic name to represent this type with. It should be more or less a lowercase version of the Java class.
      pattern - the pattern for plural forms. It's written in Skript aliases plural format. Examples :
      • fish -> fish (invariant)
      • dog&brvbar;s -> dog and dogs
      • part&brvbar;y&brvbar;ies -> party and parties (irregular plural)
      literalParser - the function that would parse literals for the given type. If the parser throws an exception on parsing, it will be caught and the type will be ignored.
      toStringFunction - the functions that converts an object of the type T to a String.Defaults to Objects.toString(Object) for other constructors.
